## ⚡ Performance Benchmark

The physics integration hot path is compiled to native machine code using
`@numba.njit(fastmath=True)`. The benchmark notebook ([`benchmark.ipynb`](benchmark.ipynb)) measures:

| Particles | Pure Python | Numba JIT | Speedup |
|-----------|-------------|-----------|---------|
| N = 500   | *run notebook* | — | **~100–300×** |
| N = 2 000 | *run notebook* | — | **~100–300×** |

> The one-time JIT compilation cost (~1–3 s) is paid once per process and then cached to disk.

Run the benchmark yourself:
```bash
jupyter notebook benchmark.ipynb
```

---

## 🚀 Installation

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/Ibrahimboutal/PSAT.git
cd PSAT

# Install the package in editable mode (includes core + dev tools)
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

---

## 🖥️ Web UI (Streamlit)

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

Then open `http://localhost:8501` in your browser.  Adjust parameters with the
sidebar sliders and click **Run Simulation** — no command line needed.

**Deploy to the cloud (free):**  
Push your repo to GitHub, connect it at [streamlit.io/cloud](https://streamlit.io/cloud), and set `app.py` as the entry point.

---

## 💻 CLI Usage

```bash
# Quick run — 500 particles, default parameters
psat --num-particles 500

# Sub-micron aerosol with animation
psat --num-particles 300 --mean-diameter 0.5e-6 --geo-std-dev 1.8 --animate

# With thermophoresis and an electric field
psat --num-particles 1000 --grad-t 500 0 0 --e-field 0 1000 0 --q-charges 5
```

### All CLI Arguments

| Argument | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `--num-particles` | 1000 | Number of Monte Carlo particles |
| `--mean-diameter` | 5e-6 | Geometric mean particle diameter (m) |
| `--geo-std-dev` | 1.5 | Geometric std dev of log-normal distribution |
| `--time` | 0.4 | Total simulation time (s) |
| `--L1` | 0.05 | Main pipe length before bifurcation (m) |
| `--theta` | π/6 | Bifurcation half-angle (radians) |
| `--grad-t` | 0 0 0 | Temperature gradient vector (K/m) |
| `--e-field` | 0 0 0 | Electric field vector (V/m) |
| `--q-charges` | 0 | Elementary charges per particle |
| `--eddy-diff` | 0.0 | Turbulent eddy diffusivity (m²/s) |
| `--save-trajectories` | off | Save & plot trajectory history |
| `--animate` | off | Render `simulation.gif` |
| `--output` | results.json | Path for statistics JSON output |

---

## 📁 Outputs

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `results.json` | Deposition efficiency, wall & outlet fractions |
| `deposition.png` | Axial wall deposition histogram |
| `trajectories.png` | Static 3-D overlay of particle paths |
| `simulation.gif` | Time-series animation *(with `--animate`)* |

